  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Deneba Crystal is a very rare blue gemstone that is
  sometimes found near underwater volcanic steam vents. Though the details =
of
  it&#8217;s formation process are unknown, geologists think that it&#8217;s
  brilliant blue color is the result of a reaction between trace elements in
  oceanic waters and the intense temperature of the volcanic vents.</span><=
span
  style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Deneba Crystal is highly prized for it&#8217;s ability =
to
  emit extremely beautiful shimmering blue light. The fine details in its
  crystal structure project incredible holographic patterns into its
  surroundings.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Any colony supplied with Deneba Crystal thus receives a=
 30%
  development bonus, over and above any other bonus. Once discovered, every
  effort should be made to control the trade of this highly valuable resour=
ce.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Occurrence: extremely rare</span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Type: Luxury Resource<span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso=
-ansi-language:
  EN-GB'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
